  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/media/13071244/italy-2019-cover.png" alt="Italy 2019 brochure" rel="486,453" /></div>
<div style="height: 15px; font-size: x-small; text-align: center;">New Inghams Italy 2019 brochure.</div>
<div> </div>
<p>Specialist tour operator Inghams has launched its Italy 2019 brochure, with more hotels than ever before!</p>
<p>The new brochure features over 200 properties across 13 regions of Italy and includes a vast range of <strong>flexible, tailor-made holiday options with local flights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Bespoke multi-centre itineraries</li>
<li>City breaks in centrally-located hotels</li>
<li>Rural retreats for relaxing escapes</li>
<li>Beach holidays in Italy’s most sought-after resorts</li>
<li>Lakes and Mountains holidays in northern Italy</li>
<li>Small group escorted tours</li>
<li>Rail holidays</li>
<li>Opera and event tickets</li>
</ul>
<p>The brochure adopts a new design with resort guides, hidden gem recommendations and tips from the experts included. Once more, new for this edition, much of the programme is bookable online at www.inghams.co.uk/italy-holidays.</p>
<p>Of the new brochure, Inghams’ Senior Product Manager for Italy, Laura Mason, says: “Our new range of exciting holidays will allow guests to get off the beaten track in 2019 and discover the real Italy. Regions like Puglia, Liguria and South East Sicily are growing in popularity, and we’re facilitating this with more choice than ever before: guests can stay in a <em>trullo </em>or an <em>agriturismo</em> property for a unique, authentic experience! Guests will also be able to seek magical experiences in more popular destinations, such as a journey on the iconic Venice Simplon-Orient-Express. We even offer the chance to book a private escorted tour - perfect for a special occasion! Our flexibility means there’s truly something to suit everyone and we look forward to welcoming all to Italy in 2019.”</p>
<p>Paul Carter, CEO, added, “We’re ecstatic to have expanded our portfolio in Italy for 2019, and we’re really looking forward to a season of positive growth.”</p>
<p><strong>Inghams offers a seven-night </strong><strong>Neapolitan Splendours escorted tour</strong><strong> from £1,495 per person. Price includes return flights and airport transfers, four-star accommodation on a half boards basis, a half-day walking tour of Sorrento, full day visits to Pompeii (including Mount Vesuvius), Capri, and the Amalfi Coast including Ravello and Amalfi.  Departure dates: 4 May 2019, 18 May 2019, 7 September 2019, 21 September 2019. For more information and to book, visit </strong><strong>www.inghams.co.uk/italy-holidays</strong><strong> or call 01483 791 115.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Inghams offers a seven-night stay in a trullo in </strong><strong>Puglia</strong><strong> from £709 per person based on two sharing. Price includes return flights, car hire, and bed &amp; breakfast accommodation in a trullo in the UNESCO Heritage Site of Alberbello, Puglia. A range of departure dates and other durations are available. For more information and to book, visit </strong><strong>www.inghams.co.uk/italy-holidays</strong><strong> or call 01483 791 115.</strong></p>
<p><strong>For more information, or to order a copy of the new brochure, visit </strong><strong>www.inghams.co.uk/italy-holidays</strong><strong> or call 01483 791 115.</strong></p>
<p><strong>-ENDS-</strong></p>
<p><strong><u>ABOUT INGHAMS<br /></u></strong>Inghams was founded by Walter Ingham in 1934, born out of his enduring passion for ski, mountaineering and walking. In 2014, Inghams celebrated its 80<sup>th</sup> year and the brand continues to pride itself on being one of the UK's leading, most experienced specialist tour operators, delivering a wide range of award-winning holidays to its loyal guests. Today, Inghams offers winter holidays to over 90 resorts in eight countries, with flights from 21 UK regional airports. It also has a popular Lakes &amp; Mountains summer holiday programme to many European destinations and a dedicated Inghams Italy programme. For more information, visit www.inghams.co.uk.          </p>
<p><strong>For media enquiries, please contact Frankie Gibson, PR Executive, on 01483 791 045 / </strong><strong>Frankie.gibson@inghams.co.uk</strong><strong> / Twitter: @Fr4nkie_90</strong></p>
<p>Follow Inghams on social media at:          <br /><strong>Facebook and Twitter:</strong> @InghamsSki / @InghamsSummer / @InghamsItaly         <br /><strong>Instagram: </strong>@InghamsHolidays / @InghamsItaly<br /><strong>YouTube:</strong> /inghamsholidays</p>
